<span id="freeTextContainer16854170218503564540">I picked up this book after reading the author&apos;s other book on mindful meditation. If you have read that book and was captured by the simple, straightforwardness style of it, you&apos;ll probably like the writing style of this book too. <br/><br/>This book delves into the eight steps to happiness and the author tries to explain in a simple, direct manner of each step. If you&apos;re curious about Buddha&apos;s teaching of the eight skills to happiness, this might be a good book to start. This book is not meant to be a v</span>
  <span id="freeText16854170218503564540" style="display:none">I picked up this book after reading the author's other book on mindful meditation. If you have read that book and was captured by the simple, straightforwardness style of it, you'll probably like the writing style of this book too. <br /><br />This book delves into the eight steps to happiness and the author tries to explain in a simple, direct manner of each step. If you're curious about Buddha's teaching of the eight skills to happiness, this might be a good book to start. This book is not meant to be a very complicated philosophical discourse, but rather, a practical, simple manual with suggestions on specific actions you can take in practicing the eight steps. </span>
