        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1603047800" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9112063887257351422">For a variety of reasons this book sat on my shelf for years after being introduced to it as part of a meditation class. I wish I had read it to completion years ago. This is essential Dhamma especially for a Western reader. It has helped me to understand the 8 fold path more deeply and in a way that I can really relate it to my life. I really appreciate the compassionate tone of Bhante G and the humanness ... how he draws on his experiences of the challenge of walking the path but how happiness</span>
  <span id="freeText9112063887257351422" style="display:none">For a variety of reasons this book sat on my shelf for years after being introduced to it as part of a meditation class. I wish I had read it to completion years ago. This is essential Dhamma especially for a Western reader. It has helped me to understand the 8 fold path more deeply and in a way that I can really relate it to my life. I really appreciate the compassionate tone of Bhante G and the humanness ... how he draws on his experiences of the challenge of walking the path but how happiness is attainable. I am very grateful for this book and know it will be one I return to again and again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9112063887257351422" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
